believe that any Content does not comply with the User guidelines, please fill out our Feedback form</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>11. Service Limitations and Modifications</h3>\r\n<p>TUTOR WIZARD will make reasonable efforts to keep the TUTOR WIZARD Service operational. However, certain technical difficulties or maintenance may, from time to time, result in temporary interruptions. To the extent permissible under applicable law, TUTOR WIZARD reserves the right, periodically and at any time, to modify or discontinue, temporarily or permanently, functions and features of the TUTOR WIZARD Service, with or without notice, all without liability to you, except where prohibited by law, for any interruption, modification, or discontinuation of the TUTOR WIZARD Service or any function or feature thereof. Notwithstanding the foregoing, if you have prepaid fees for Paid Subscriptions that TUTOR WIZARD permanently discontinues prior to the end of the Pre-Paid Period (defined in the Payments and cancellations section), TUTOR WIZARD will refund you the prepaid fees for the Pre-Paid Period after such discontinuation. You understand, agree, and accept that TUTOR WIZARD has no obligation to maintain, support, upgrade, or update the Service, or to provide all or any specific content through the Service. This section will be enforced to the extent permissible by applicable law. TUTOR WIZARD and/or the owners of any Content may, from time to time, remove any such Content without notice to the extent permitted by applicable law.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>12. TUTOR WIZARD Support Community</h3>\r\n<p>The TUTOR WIZARD Support Community is a place for discussions and exchange of information, tips, and other materials related to the TUTOR WIZARD Service. In order to use the TUTOR WIZARD Support Community, you must (1) have an existing TUTOR WIZARD account; and (2) authenticate your TUTOR WIZARD account for use on the Support Community (a “TUTOR WIZARD Support Account”). Instructions for creating a TUTOR WIZARD Support Account can be found on the Community registration page. In addition to the Agreements, you also agree to adhere to the TUTOR WIZARD user guidelines that stated in these terms when using the TUTOR WIZARD Support Community. If you do not agree to the Agreements or the Support Community Guidelines, you may not use the TUTOR WIZARD Support Community.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>12.1. TUTOR WIZARD Support Accounts</h3>\r\n<p>By creating a TUTOR WIZARD Support Account, you confirm that any registration information that you submit to TUTOR WIZARD is true, accurate, and complete and that you will update such information in order to keep it current. It is strictly prohibited to include information in your profile that suggests that you are a TUTOR WIZARD employee or moderator or to otherwise pose as such an employee or moderator when using the TUTOR WIZARD Support Community. You also acknowledge and agree that TUTOR WIZARD may remove or reclaim your username at any time if TUTOR WIZARD in its absolute discretion considers such action appropriate.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>12.2. No Official Support</h3>\r\n<p>No User Content or other content posted by TUTOR WIZARD employees, moderators and/or representatives on the TUTOR WIZARD Support Community should be construed as official support provided by TUTOR WIZARD. For details regarding official support, please see the ways to Contact Us. Any content provided or made available to you on the TUTOR WIZARD Support Community by TUTOR WIZARD employees, moderators, and/or representatives is provided on an “as is” basis without warranties of any kind.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You acknowledge that opinions expressed in User Content on the TUTOR WIZARD Support Community are those of contributors of such User Content only and do not reflect the opinions or policies of TUTOR WIZARD or any of its officers, shareholders, employees, agents, directors, subsidiaries, affiliates, suppliers, or licensors.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>13. Customer Support</h3>\r\n<p>For customer support with account-related and payment-related questions (“Customer Support Queries”), please contact our customer service department using the details provided on the Contact Us section of our website or message section in the web portal. We will use reasonable endeavours to respond to all Customer Support Queries within a reasonable time frame but we make no guarantees or warranties of any kind that any Customer Support Queries will be responded to within any particular time frame and/or that we will be able to satisfactorily answer any such queries.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>14. Payments, Cancellations &amp; Refunds</h3>\r\n<p>Subscriptions can be purchased either by (1) paying a monthly subscription fee (“Monthly Period”); or (2) paying a termly fee of three payments spread over 12 months (“Termly Period”); or (3) paying an annual fee upfront for full access for 12 months (“Annual Period”).</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n When you register with a Monthly, Termly or Annual Period Subscription you consent to get access to TUTOR WIZARD services. Tutor Wizard will activate your account for your usage at the earliest possible opportunity. Please ensure that any registration information (mainly billing details) that you submit to TUTOR WIZARD is true, accurate, and complete and that you will update such information in order to keep it current. If not, it will may expand the activation time due to the data verification process (where applicable)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Monthly &amp; Termly Period payment terms to TUTOR WIZARD will automatically renew at the end of the subscription period, unless you cancel your Paid Subscription through your user account before the end of the current subscription period. The cancellation will take effect the day after the last day of the current subscription period. However, if you cancel your monthly or termly payment and/or terminate any of the Agreements (1) after you have